Scyramathia carpenteri

is known from the type locality, "sandy chalk of the Holtenia ground" [= between North Scotland and the Faeroe Islands] (
Carpenter et al. 1870
; Norman, in 
Thomson 1873
; 
Reiswig and Champagne 1995
), South Iceland (
Hansen 1908
), Southwest Faeroe Islands, South of Norway, West of British Isles (
Clark 1986
).
